The paper deals with security games, which are a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the spread of attacks and contagion, which are topics in social networks and network science (cs.SI). The paper also deals with defense strategies, which fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The use of heuristic strategies and optimization algorithms suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the study of network structures and their impact on the efficiency of strategies suggests the involvement of network science (cs.NI).
